It will only fit AK type rifles, including models WASR, AK-47S, MAK-90, and similar chambered in 7.62x39 caliber. Not for sale to civilian residents of Aurora IL, California, Colorado, Connecticut, Cook County / Chicago IL, Oak Park IL, District of Colombia, Hawaii, South Bend IN, Maryland, Massachusetts, New Jersey, New York, Ohio, or any jurisdiction where 31 round or higher capacity magazines are restricted for law enforcement only.

title: For Sale/Trade:  VZ2008 (VZ58)
postcontent:
"The Maryland legal AK47"

This is a Czechoslovakian designed rifle. In short Czechoslovakia did not want to follow in suite with the Russians and came up with their own AK. In fact they even had their own cartridge early on with their VZ 52 (their version of an SKS), 7.62x45, but later on adopted the Russian 7.62x39.

This a short piston, striker fire operated rifle. As opposed to the Russian long piston, hammer operated AK. A unique feature to this gun is that it has a last round bolt hold open mechanism, which the AK does not. Also an AK tends to shoot the brass more to the 3 o'clock position, whereas the VZ tends to shoot them straight up. People have said that due to the shorter travel of the bolt in the VZ the recoil is a lessened. Not quite sure how valid that is, as both seem to be about the same to me. 

This specific rifle has been fired approximately 600 times, as in 600 rounds, not 600 individual trips (in case there is any confusion). After each range trip, it has been sprayed down with copious amounts of CLP and wiped down for a general cleaning. Not to military white glove standard, if you are picky about those things. 

Included with this rifle are:
Magazines (x3)
Ammo (if so desired)(must increase trade or money value of course)

Anyways on to the "asking" price. I am in no hurry to sell this gun, but I do enjoy my AK47 much more. I just want to test the waters and see what I can get. 

Not sure why I am only allowed to upload one picture, but please do contact me for more.

The Commando Special, not to be confused with the WWII Commando version of the Official Police, had the matte black finish and used a rubber grip used only on the matte finish guns, and only for a few years.

Internally, the Commando Special was fitted and finished as well as the polished Detective Special model.

title: For Sale/Trade:  S&W 422 target pistol  SALE  PENDING
postcontent: S&W 422 with two 12 round magazines in like new condition. This gun appears to have been shot very little. The 422 is unique in design from the barrel being low in the frame just above the trigger guard. The barrel lowered allows the shooter to get back on target quickly because of very little muzzle jump making it a great target competition pistol. Reading the forums on this gun it's said by many to be the finest 22 target pistol in it's class with the best quality. Unfortunately building quality costs money and S&W discontinued the 422 because of the cost to produce it. They were made from 1987-1997. These are nice shooting guns that are economical and fun to shoot. Compare on Gunbroker.com for $399-$450. PP or cpl required
